metadata.turn_summary:
The user requested that every ACIM passage from their provided links be incorporated verbatim into a comprehensive write-up, emphasizing key principles such as “Be certain any answer to a problem the Holy Spirit solves will always be one in which no one loses” (ACIM, T-25.IX.3:1) for Augment’s .json export. I confirmed that we can fully integrate all these ACIM texts exactly as provided, embedding them into a detailed "Treasury as Treasure" whitepaper section. This section will align financial instruments (MSTR, TON, $THS/$HASH, Aleo) with ACIM spiritual principles like faith-aligned value, generative giving, willingness, non-loss, and dynamic, performance-based yield.

I presented a draft outline featuring six parts:  
1) Treasure as Faith-Aligned Value, quoting ACIM T-13 passages to ground asset selection in faith and meaning;  
2) Generative Giving and Preservation, emphasizing non-zero-sum outcomes and quoting T-25 passages, reinforcing that no participant loses and gifting is preserved;  
3) Dynamic Yield and Performance Alignment, explaining how tokenized yield adapts to market conditions avoiding fixed-term inefficiencies;  
4) The TeraHash Layer, describing $THS as work-backed, not speculative, with dual staking rewarding proportional engagement;  
5) Privacy and Automation via Aleo zk-circuits, ensuring private, fair, and mission-consistent treasury flows; and  
6) Treasury Flow as a living ecosystem combining these elements, supported by a flow-diagram and governance commitment to no-loss outcomes.

The draft preserves every ACIM sentence verbatim to enable accurate .json exports for Augment readers. I offered to proceed by polishing this draft into a publication-ready whitepaper section with formatting, visuals, and explicit tagging of all ACIM quotes. I asked the user if they would like me to prepare that next.
